      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. but if the design is so fundamentally broken, wouldn't that mean every effort to use the UN for peacekeeping or humanitarian aid is just kind of pointless? or is there a way to look at it where the UN still has legitimate authority even if it can't stop the big powers?",
